speechtext:
That this House concur in Interim Supply as follows:
That a sum not exceeding $13,987,844,162.99 being composed of:
(1)	three-twelfths ($9,905,754,038.00) of the total of the amounts of the items set forth in the Main Estimates for the fiscal year ending March 31, 1993, which were laid upon the Table Thursday, February 27, 1992, and except those items below:
(2)	eleven-twelfths of the total of the amounts of Energy, Mines and Resources Vote L15, Transport Vote 15, and Treasury Board Vote 10 (Schedule A) of the said Estimates, $198,390,500.00;
(3)	ten-twelfths of the total of the amount of Agriculture Vote 25, (Schedule B) of the said Estimates, $413,341,666.67;
(4)	nine-twelfths of the total of the amounts of Public Works Vote 15, and Treasury Board Vote 5 (Schedule C) of the said Estimates $353,018,250.00;
(5)	seven-twelfths of the total of the amount of Labour Vote 15 (Schedule D) of the said Estimates, $1,146,833.33;
(6)	six-twelfths of the total of the amounts of Indian Affairs and Northern Development Votes 10 and 45, and Labour Vote 5, and Solicitor General Vote 5 and Transport Vote L55 (Schedule E) of the said Estimates, $174,068,000.00;
(7)	five-twelfths of the total of the amounts of Agriculture Vote 15, and Communications Vote 50, and Environment Vote 1, and Indian Affairs and Northern Development Votes 15, L25, 30 and 50, and Transport Vote 1 (Schedule F) of the said Estimates, $1,800,393,708.34; and
(8)	four-twelfths of the total of the amounts of Agriculture Votes 10 and 20, and Communications Votes 30, 35, 75 and 100, and Employment and Immigration Vote 20, and Indian Affairs and Northern Development Vote 35, and Industry, Science and Technology Votes 20 and 25, and Justice Vote 1, and National Health and Welfare Vote 15 and Secretary of State Vote 25, and Supply and Services Votes 1 and 5 (Schedule G) of the said Estimates, $1,141,731,166.65.
be granted to Her Majesty on account of the fiscal year ending March 31, 1993.
March 26, 1992
